        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Currently, when you don't set the partial for paginationControl, it just throws an exception. But, IMHO, you could render a decent paginator without it being required. Say\n\n{code} \n<ul class=\"paginator\">\n  <li class=\"first\"><a href=\"#\">&laquo;<\/a><\/li>\n  <li class=\"previous\"><a href=\"#\">&lsaquo;<\/a><\/li>\n  <li><a href=\"#\">1<\/a><\/li>\n  <li><a href=\"#\">2<\/a><\/li>\n  <li class=\"current\"><span>4<\/span><\/li>\n  <li><a href=\"#\">5<\/a><\/li>\n  <li class=\"next\"><a href=\"#\">&rsaquo;<\/a><\/li>\n  <li class=\"last\"><a href=\"#\">&raquo;<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n{code} \n\nThis would lower the requirements for using it."
        },
